# =====================================================
# RULES
# =====================================================
# 1. Environment files are ALWAYS ignored
# 2. API keys NEVER go to git
# 3. Database dumps are ignored
# 4. Private keys are ignored
# 5. Temporary files are ignored
# 6. Build artifacts are ignored
# 7. Node modules are ignored (if using Node.js)
# 8. IDE configurations are ignored
# 9. OS-specific files are ignored
# 10. Logs and caches are ignored

# =====================================================
# SAFETY: If you accidentally committed any secrets,
# IMMEDIATELY ROTATE THE KEYS!
# Run: git rm -r --cached . && git add . && git commit -m "Remove secrets"
# Then regenerate all API keys
# =====================================================
